The MotorMechs and Technicians Association of Nigeria (MOMTAN) has congratulated President-elect, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress (APC) on his victory at the recent presidential election in the country. The association also congratulated the Vice President-elect, Senator Kashim Shettima, on his victory at the election. In a letter addressed to Tinubu, the National President of the association, Alhaji Maruf Adebayo Arowolo, described the victory as confidence reposed in his capacity to take the country to the next level. He said the victory is a positive development in Nigeria’s democratic journey. He urged Tinubu to deepen Nigeria’s democratic process, advance social democracy, and guarantee a better life for all. Arowolo urged the President-elect to work towards the betterment of the citizens’ lives as well as ensure the country meets her historic responsibility to Africans. He added that the victory is a call to duty and urged the President-elect to consolidate on the infrastructure development and progress that has been recorded in the country. He appealed to Tinubu to implement policies and programmes that will improve the fortunes of the automotive industry in the country.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ He commended the Nigerian voters for their participation, patience and resilience in voting in the election.